[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = GIFImages","category":"page"},{"location":"#GIFImages","page":"Home","title":"GIFImages","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This is the documentation for GIFImages.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"GIFImages.jl provides support for decoding and encoding GIF images.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Usage","page":"Home","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"For decoding purposes, GIFImages.jl currently supports gif_decode which  decode the GIF image as colorant matrix. The source data needs to be a filename.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Arguments","page":"Home","title":"Arguments","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"filepath::AbstractString : Path to the gif file\nuse_localpalette::Bool=false : While decoding, using this argument use of local colormap or global colormap for a particular slice can be specified. Gif files are palette based and have a global colormap(max 256 colors) but slices/images in gif can have their own local colormap specific to a particular slice/image. These colormap can be used to decode a image if use_localpalette as true.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Examples","page":"Home","title":"Examples","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> using GIFImages, Downloads\n\njulia> path = \"test/data/fire.gif\"\n\"test/data/fire.gif\"\n\njulia> img = gif_decode(path)\n60×30×33 Array{RGB{N0f8},3} with eltype RGB{N0f8}","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"For encoding, GIFImages.jl provides gif_encode which encode the GIF colorant matrix to file. ","category":"page"},{"location":"#Arguments-2","page":"Home","title":"Arguments","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"filepath : Name of the file to which image is written.\nimg : 3D GIF colorant matrix which has structure of height* width * numofimages and all the images are present as slices of the 3D matrix \ncolormapnum : Specifies the number of colors to be used for the global colormap","category":"page"},{"location":"#Examples-2","page":"Home","title":"Examples","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> using GIFImages, Downloads\n\njulia> path = \"test/data/fire.gif\"\n\"test/data/fire.gif\"\n\njulia> img = gif_decode(path)\n60×30×33 Array{RGB{N0f8},3} with eltype RGB{N0f8}\n\njulia> gif_encode(\"fire.gif\", img)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [GIFImages]","category":"page"},{"location":"#GIFImages.gif_decode-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"Home","title":"GIFImages.gif_decode","text":"gif_decode(filepath::AbstractString; use_localpalette=false)\n\nDecode the GIF image as colorant matrix. The source data needs to be a filename.\n\nArguments\n\nfilepath::AbstractString : Path to the gif file\nuse_localpalette::Bool=false : While decoding, using this argument use of local colormap or global colormap for a particular slice can be specified. Gif files are palette based and have a global colormap(max 256 colors) but slices/images in gif can have their own local colormap specific to a particular slice/image.\n\nExamples\n\n```jl julia> using GIFImages, Downloads\n\njulia> path = \"test/data/fire.gif\" \"test/data/fire.gif\"\n\njulia> img = gif_decode(path) 60×30×33 Array{RGB{N0f8},3} with eltype RGB{N0f8}\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GIFImages.gif_encode-Tuple{AbstractString, AbstractArray}","page":"Home","title":"GIFImages.gif_encode","text":"gif_encode(filepath::AbstractString, img::AbstractArray; num::Int = 64)\n\nEncode the GIF colorant matrix to file. \n\nArguments\n\nfilepath : Name of the file to which image is written.\nimg : 3D GIF colorant matrix which has structure of heightwidthnumofimags and all the images are present as slices of the 3D matrix \ncolormapnum : Specifies the number of colors to be used for the global colormap\n\nExamples\n\njulia> using GIFImages, Downloads\n\njulia> path = \"test/data/fire.gif\"\n\"test/data/fire.gif\"\n\njulia> img = gif_decode(path)\n60×30×33 Array{RGB{N0f8},3} with eltype RGB{N0f8}\n\njulia> gif_encode(\"fire.gif\", img)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
